text: Barany Bugor () is a rural locality (a selo) in Semibugrinsky Selsoviet, Kamyzyaksky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 225 as of 2010. There are 3 streets. == Geography == It is located on the Bolda River. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kamyzyaksky District
title: Barany Bugor
